The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, delivered a speech at the "Ministerial to Promote a Future of Peace and Security in the Middle East" in Warsaw, Poland. He highlighted the common threats faced by nations in the Middle East, particularly radical Islamist terrorism and authoritarian regimes that support it. Pence emphasized the need for unity and cooperation to address these challenges and forge a brighter future of security and prosperity in the region. He also condemned the Iranian regime as the leading state sponsor of terrorism, highlighting its destabilizing activities and human rights abuses. Pence called on European partners to withdraw from the Iran nuclear deal and join the United States in exerting economic and diplomatic pressure on Iran. He expressed the United States' commitment to achieving a lasting peace between Israelis and Palestinians, as well as its support for allies and human rights in the region. Pence concluded by urging all peace-loving nations to stand together and work towards a shared future in the Middle East.